# Next-Phase Gate Review

Use this rule when the task is a phase-start review, a pre-PR or pre-merge gate, a large AI-generated change review, or a risky-surface review involving schemas, migrations, RLS, authentication, AI parsing, prompt contracts, calendar writes, environment/config, or deployment.

Do not treat this as an every-run checklist for routine tasks.

When it applies:

- use `docs/skills/next-phase-gate-review.md`
- keep the review diagnostic only
- do not implement fixes unless explicitly asked
- distinguish blockers from optional cleanup
- prefer small, scoped cleanup over broad refactors
